{"nodes":[{"nodeID":"1083","text":"The newly  clean  addict may also feel violated traumatised and betrayed by their detention","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:20:56"},{"nodeID":"1454","text":"His suggestion is disturbing unworkable and potentially dangerous","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:16"},{"nodeID":"1457","text":"Locking up addicts against their will would not only violate their rights; it would be likely to prove counter-productive","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:16"},{"nodeID":"1469","text":"an excellent emotional recipe for getting straight back on the gear again.","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:19"},{"nodeID":"1470","text":"People use drugs to block out painful underlying problems and those problems won't dissolve after a mandatory drying-out period","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:19"},{"nodeID":"1471","text":"Forced detection is harmful under this point of view","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:19"},{"nodeID":"1472","text":"However much they want to help if your loved ones have conspired to have you thrown in the slammer against your will - and many addicts will see it that way - you're hardly going to pop round to their place for a cuppa and a chat when you get out.","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:19"},{"nodeID":"1473","text":"Families of drug addicts know that addiction chips away at healthy relationships","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:19"},{"nodeID":"1474","text":"When drugs take over as a priority the user becomes increasingly isolated from those around them - partners siblings parents employers","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:19"},{"nodeID":"1475","text":"Even supportive friends can find themselves shut out","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:19"},{"nodeID":"1476","text":"Drug buddies are always there but it becomes very difficult to maintain relationships outside the drug culture.","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:19"},{"nodeID":"1477","text":"What is counter productive can be dangerous","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:19"},{"nodeID":"1478","text":"Phychological shocks are a cause of the use of drug","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:19"},{"nodeID":"1479","text":"forcibly locking up addicts could do further serious harm to these relationships","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:19"},{"nodeID":"1480","text":"The resulting social isolation often triggers more drug use.","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:19"},{"nodeID":"1481","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:19","scheme":"Example"},{"nodeID":"1482","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:20","scheme":"Example"},{"nodeID":"1483","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:20"},{"nodeID":"1484","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:20","scheme":"Example"},{"nodeID":"1485","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:21"},{"nodeID":"1486","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:21","scheme":"Example"},{"nodeID":"1487","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:21","scheme":"Example"},{"nodeID":"1488","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:21","scheme":"Example"},{"nodeID":"1489","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:22"},{"nodeID":"1490","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:22","scheme":"CauseToEffect"},{"nodeID":"1491","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:22:22"}],"edges":[{"edgeID":"1358","fromID":"1469","toID":"1481","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1359","fromID":"1481","toID":"1457","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1360","fromID":"1470","toID":"1482","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1361","fromID":"1482","toID":"1457","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1362","fromID":"1471","toID":"1483","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1363","fromID":"1483","toID":"1457","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1364","fromID":"1472","toID":"1484","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1365","fromID":"1484","toID":"1479","formEdgeID":